On Fri, 26 Jul 2002, Adrian Pillow wrote:

> I use the Permatex Anti-Seize gray stuff (NAPA and most other auto shops
> have it).  Does not drip or run and protects from the star adjusters
> freezing.

I've used this too...and found that (in my case) it seems to gum and
freeze up after a few months. Road and brake dust seem to be a hardener
for it.  I went back to grease. :)


